<div class="large-12 small-12 columns">
  <%= render 'cms/available_locales/side_nav' %>

  <div class="medium-8 small-12 columns">
    <h5 class="text-center">Edit Landing Page</h5>
    <div class="callout panel">
      <%= render 'cms/available_locales/landing_pages/originated_form' %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="large-2 medium-2 columns">
    <div class="text-right">
      <%= link_to [:cms, @available_locale, @landing_page],
        method: :delete,
        data: { confirm: "Are you sure?" },
        class: "tiny alert button radius" do %>
        <%= fa_icon 'trash' %>
        Delete Landing Page
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <hr/>
    <p>The URL for this page has been generated
    based on the title. If you change the title,
    you'll see the URL
    after editing the page.</p>
    <p>The current URL for this page is:</p>
    <p><%= link_to landing_page_url(@landing_page, locale: @landing_page.original_locale.key) do %>
      <%= landing_page_url(@landing_page, locale: @landing_page.original_locale.key) %>
    <% end %>
    </p>
    <h6>Forms</h6>
    <p>To insert a form on your landing page,
    put one of these snippets in one of the
    content boxes:<p>
<pre>
~contact_form~
~lead_form~
</pre>
    <p>In both cases, the form will be
    emailed to the address(es) defined in the
    <%= link_to "Site Setting", [:cms, @available_locale, :site_settings] %>
    named "leadgen-recipients".
    This setting can be a single email address
    or a comma-separated list of email addresses.</p>
  </div>
</div>
